<title type="html"><![CDATA[7/13 Reasons to Remain Single / Pension reform]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=55&amp;p=59#p59"><![CDATA[
Host : Morris<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session I.  Reasons to Remain Single</span><br />Pleas watch the following video, and come to the meeting to share your opinions:<br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=350qUmbcAZU" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=350qUmbcAZU</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1. Do you agree that “romantic love is a dangerous illusion” as said in the video? Why or why not?<br />2. Do you agree that “no one think their partner is terrific after a while” as said in the video? How long have you met your current partner? Is he/she still terrific? Why or why not?<br />3. Why are pros and cons of besing single?  Do think being single is better than getting married? Why or why not?<br /><br /><br />**************************************************************************************************************<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session II.  Pension reform</span><br /><br />Please read the following news and come to the meeting to share your opinions, <br /><a href="http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/national/national-news/2017/07/01/499133/president-tsai.htm" class="postlink">http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/national/national-news/2017/07/01/499133/president-tsai.htm</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1. Do you think the passage of pension reform in the Legislative Yaun for civil servants, public school teachers and political appointees are sucessful? Why or why not?<br />2. Afer the reform, what will be the possible impacts or changes on the people reformed and the whole country? <br />3. What is your plan for your retirement? How can we live a better retired life?<br /><br />**************************************************************************************************************<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Agenda</span><br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:05pm discussion session (35 mins)<br />8:05 ~ 8:20pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:20 ~ 8:25pm Regrouping &amp; instruction giving<br />(Session II)<br />8:25 ~ 8:35pm Taking a 10 minutes break (Intermission)<br />8:35 ~ 9:10pm discussion session (35 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~ 9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />摩斯漢堡明曜店 (地下室)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運 - 板南線 - 忠孝敦化站 (步行約5分鐘)<br /><a href="http://www.ipeen.com.tw/shop/32318/" class="postlink">http://www.ipeen.com.tw/shop/32318/</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=49">josh</a> — Mon Jul 10, 2017 1:36 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
